text: Malik Wasif Mazhar Raan is a Pakistani politician who is member of the Provincial Assembly of Punjab. ==Political career== Wasif Mazhar Raan contested by-election on 31 March 2019 from constituency PP-218 (Multan-VIII) of Provincial Assembly of Punjab on the ticket of Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf. He won the election by the majority of 7,502 votes over the runner up Malik Muhammad Arshad Raan of Pakistan Peoples Party. He garnered 46,988 votes while Arshad Raan received 39,486 votes. ==References== Category:Living people Category:Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf MPAs (Punjab) Category:Punjab MPAs 2018–2023 Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
